text: Sandra Dale "Sandy" Dennis (April 27, 1937-March 2, 1992) was an American actress. She received two Tony Awards for acting. She performed mostly in theater and movies. Her most notable movies included Sweet November (1968), The Out-of-Towners (1970) and The Indian Runner. Dennis was born in Nebraska. She died of ovarian cancer in Westport, Connecticut.
